The paper describes a software package for visualizing large scale volumetric data using virtual reality head-mounted displays. This involves developing highly optimized data flow and volume rendering pipelines, as well as tools for advanced data exploration, annotation, and cataloguing. Given this focus on graphics and visualization, as well as the use of computer vision techniques for image analysis, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.GR (Graphics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
